@node "history" "History"

@{b}V1.9 (September 2008)@{ub}

  - Fixed null-pointer accesses that occurred when a notification reply was
    received after EndNotify() had been called.
  - Fixed bugs related to reading and writing a file at the same time.
  - Files that are protected from deletion can no longer be overwritten with
    a new file of the same name.
  - Changed default volume name from 'RAM Disc' to 'RAM Disk'.
  - Changed licence from GPL to LGPL.

@{b}V1.8 (August 2006)@{ub}

  - Fixed a null-pointer access that could occur when memory could not be
    allocated.

@{b}V1.7 (April 2003)@{ub}

  - Fixed ExAll() bug (thanks to Andreas Kürzinger).

@{b}V1.6 (March 2003)@{ub}

  - Now uses memory pools.
  - Implemented ACTION_EXAMINE_ALL and ACTION_EXAMINE_ALL_END.
  - Bug fix: notification occurred immediately when files were overwritten.
  - Bug fix: volume could be dismounted when root directory was locked.
  - Hard links can now be deleted when the object they refer to is in use.

@{b}V1.5 (January 2003)@{ub}

  - No longer possible for a new file to overwrite an empty directory.
  - Fixed small error in reported disk usage.
  - SetDate on links works now.
  - Redesigned notification code to make it faster.
  - Fixed bug triggered by zero-length writes (thanks to Vinnny).
  - Fixed various notification bugs.
  - Fixed memory leak in notification code (thanks to Dietmar Eilert).
  - Shortened list of advantages to reflect improvements in official RAM
    disk.
  - Documentation now advises that Workbench problems are OS 3.0/3.1
    specific.
  - New icons.

@{b}V1.4 (March 2002)@{ub}

  - Moving an object to a different directory now works properly.
  - Rewrote ACTION_SEEK and ACTION_READ to fix several bugs.
  - Bug fix: in certain cases, a file could be created in a non-existent
    directory.

@{b}V1.3 (February 2002)@{ub}

  - Bug fix: renaming the disk could cause crashes.
  - Renaming the disk now affects block-usage reports.

@{b}V1.2 (January 2002)@{ub}

  - Less strict for better compatibility.

@{b}V1.1 (March 2001)@{ub}

  - First release.

@endnode


